VERENA - Basic Education Minister Angie Motshekga has admitted to weaknesses in providing safe and reliable scholar transport.She says there are gaps in implementing and monitoring the system.Motshekga was speaking in Mpumalanga at a memorial service for 18 pupils who died on their way home from school nearly two weeks ago.Seven pupils survived the crash.WATCH: Memorial service for Verena crash victimsThe children were traveling in a minibus taxi hired by their parents.Motshekga said parents must check that the vehicles transporting their children are compliant with the scholar transport policy.Earlier in the day, the grieving families received the DNA results of their loved ones.All the bodies were positively identified.A mass funeral is planned for Saturday.eNCA